# Slate Language Reference

## A complete demonstration of every visual element in the Slate markup system.

---

::: section Overview align=center
  # Project Dashboard
  ## Real-time analytics, diagrams, forms, and structured layouts compiled from plain text.
:::

---

// =============================================
// SECTION 1: Typography and Text Elements
// =============================================

### Typography

Standard paragraph text renders cleanly with system fonts and comfortable line height.

- Bullet point items begin with a dash
- Each item renders with a clean dot marker
- Lists support unlimited depth and length
* Asterisk bullets also work identically

> Blockquotes are prefixed with the greater-than symbol and render with a left accent border.

[x] Checked checkbox item with a filled square marker
[x] Another completed task in the checklist
[ ] Unchecked checkbox item with an empty square marker
[ ] Pending task waiting for completion

